Hate to break it to you, but in Velious Mage and Necro pets = little more than armed, wet pieces of paper. When things hit for 400+ and Rampage/Flurry a pet goes down faster than a.....well, nevermind. The game is about efficiency, yes, but it is also about fun. Ask any Mage or Enchanter or Shaman is they actually ENJOY themselves on these big raids. I'm pretty sure the answer will be no. Enchanters and Shamans have been reduced to buff dispensers, most of their class defining abilites are useless in the big fights. Enchanters will C2, Gift of Brilliance casters and Rune/Speed tanks, then they're pretty much done. They may get to throw in a Tash or 2 if they're lucky, but other than that they're just 1 more person. Shamans have their HP/Stat/AC buffs they pass around (Ever seen a shaman break down because of his buffing duties and how mundane/maddening they are? Not a pretty thing), then after that they Malo/Malasini. If they're even more lucky they get to recast slow about 40 times until it sticks, sometimes dying repeatedly in the process. And Mages, well a Mage's job starts and ends at CoH. They may cast a few token pets during the fight, but other than that they're glorified intra-zone teleportation (and you people whine about US being taxies).<br>
