<br>
The Markar's Discord spell has had it's drop rate increased DRAMATICALLY, you can easily find this off of the Sebilite Juggernauts in the area surorunding Trakanon's Lair. It's a pretty nifty spell, long stun and decent ratio.<br>
<br>
AS for your assumption that Lures are, quote: &quot;BULLSHIT IMO,&quot; you must have very little idea what a godsend these spells have been for us. Would it be nice to have our regular nukes hit the Velious uber-MOBs? (Which in some cases they do, although these instances are limited) IT would be nice, but it won't happen. Lures allow us to hit pretty much ANYTHING in the game. The ratio isn't great, but it's not crap either. It's about the same as some of our pre-50 dd's, and can still allow you to get 10-12 of them off on a full bar of mana with C2 (From the lovely buffing Enchanters). The Bane spells are not the best spells int he game, but they are definitely very nice. The best mana/damage ratio of all our nukes with no resist check, they allow us to do LARGE amounts of damage in a short amount of time. The peridot cost is negligible at the level and game stage you get these spells, most if not all guilds will pay the price for the peridots. These spells are great for the fights they were designed for, mainly the HUGE HP Velious fights. Kland/Zland hardly count, with our regular Lures we can do significant damage to these 2 dragons. The Bane spells are designed for the upper tier fights in Temple of Veeshan and vs the large Giants like Velkator. The main probelm I see with the Bane spells is the faction system. It should be entirely possible for a Wizard to get both of these spells without massive faction work. As a Kael-alligned Wizard I have my Dragon's Bane, but I should still be able to get the Giant's bane to be used on the non-Kael giants.<br>
